str2: The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.
A soldier. From a presumed derivative of the same as stratia; a camper-out, i.e. A warrior.
Counsel, deliberate wisdom, decree. From boulomai; volition, i.e. advice, or purpose.
In order that, so that. Probably from the same as the former part of heautou; in order that.

parse: Verb - Aorist Subjunctive Active - 3rd Person Plural
str2: To put to death, kill; fig: I abolish. From apo and kteino; to kill outright; figuratively, to destroy.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.
A prisoner, captive. From the same as desmoterion; a captive.
Not, lest. A primary particle of qualified negation; not, lest; also (whereas ou expects an affirmative one) whether.

parse: Interrogative / Indefinite Pronoun - Nominative Masculine Singular
str2: Any one, some one, a certain one or thing. An enclitic indefinite pronoun; some or any person or object.

parse: Verb - Aorist Participle Active - Nominative Masculine Singular
str2: To swim out (of the water). From ek and kolumbao; to escape by swimming.

parse: Verb - Aorist Subjunctive Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: To escape by flight. From dia and pheugo; to flee through, i.e. Escape.
